WEBVTT

00:00:02.720 --> 00:00:03.709
<i>Previously on</i> The O.C.<i>:</i>

00:00:03.880 --> 00:00:05.233
- Hi, Theresa.
- Hi, Marissa.

00:00:05.400 --> 00:00:06.992
- Eddie.
- I'm looking for Theresa.

00:00:07.160 --> 00:00:08.798
- We're engaged.
- Engaged?

00:00:08.960 --> 00:00:11.838
- You look good.
- I'm Marissa's mother. You're a student.

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:14.036
- You mean it's over?
- No, I'll see you tonight.

00:00:14.200 --> 00:00:15.758
A friend's in trouble.
I want you to help him.

00:00:15.920 --> 00:00:16.989
Uncle Shaun.
In that room...

00:00:17.160 --> 00:00:19.515
...you accidentally stumbled
into were documents...

00:00:19.680 --> 00:00:21.750
...containing information
valuable to Caleb.

00:00:21.920 --> 00:00:24.150
- Construction's a dirty business.
- My answer's no.

00:00:24.320 --> 00:00:25.958
And Kirsten? She's complicit in this.

00:00:26.120 --> 00:00:27.553
- Do you love her?
- I don't know.

00:00:27.720 --> 00:00:28.835
Be ready to fight for her.

00:00:29.040 --> 00:00:30.678
- I don't want you to go.
- Why don't I want to go?

00:00:32.720 --> 00:00:34.836
- But what kind of kiss was it?
- I don't know.

00:00:35.000 --> 00:00:36.877
A kiss. My lips, Theresa's lips. A kiss.

00:00:37.040 --> 00:00:39.429
Lips. Now, that's interesting.
Was there tongue?

00:00:39.600 --> 00:00:41.352
- I'm not answering that.
- Why?

00:00:41.520 --> 00:00:43.431
- You really want to know?
- No.

00:00:43.600 --> 00:00:46.194
But just tell me this:
What level of kiss are we talking?

00:00:46.400 --> 00:00:48.391
Was it like a Christina-Madonna peck?

00:00:48.560 --> 00:00:50.596
Or was it a Britney-Madonna
sort of smooch?

00:00:50.760 --> 00:00:54.150
Or was it like a full-on
Al and Tipper Gore lip-Iock?

00:00:54.320 --> 00:00:56.709
- It was just a kiss.
- Okay. So you guys a couple now?

00:00:56.880 --> 00:01:00.475
Is she staying here? If so, where's she
gonna live? How? What's her credit like?

00:01:00.640 --> 00:01:04.315
What sort of lease is she looking to sign?
Are we talking a year or month-to-month?

00:01:04.480 --> 00:01:06.710
- Or is she looking to buy?
- There's no lease, okay?

00:01:06.880 --> 00:01:08.791
So then what? She goes back?
What do you do?

00:01:08.960 --> 00:01:10.518
Commute back and forth from Chino?

00:01:10.680 --> 00:01:12.716
If you're commuting,
whose car you gonna take?

00:01:12.880 --> 00:01:15.917
How you gonna pay for gas?
What freeway is your freeway of choice?

00:01:16.080 --> 00:01:19.914
You gonna take the 55 to the 5?
Or the 91 to the 71? If you take the 71...

00:01:20.200 --> 00:01:22.031
- Just, whoa.
- Okay. I'll just whoa.

00:01:22.200 --> 00:01:25.636
You guys kissed, and I think you should
have a plan, because it's a big deal.

00:01:25.800 --> 00:01:27.552
- You're making it a big deal.
- Really?

00:01:27.720 --> 00:01:29.199
I don't even know when
I'd see her again.

00:01:29.360 --> 00:01:31.430
- Hi.
- Theresa. Hey.

00:01:31.600 --> 00:01:33.511
Hey. We were just
discussing your plan.

00:01:33.680 --> 00:01:35.318
- What plan?
- Yeah, exactly.

00:01:35.480 --> 00:01:37.948
I had the morning off,
thought you'd need a ride to school.

00:01:38.120 --> 00:01:39.314
- Oh, yeah. Great.
- Yeah.

00:01:39.480 --> 00:01:41.948
- I hope it's okay, me stopping by.
- It's fine. Come on.

00:01:42.120 --> 00:01:44.509
- Yeah. Sure. Why wouldn't it be?
- Okay.

00:01:44.960 --> 00:01:47.713
- Marissa. Hello.
- Hey.

00:01:48.800 --> 00:01:52.759
- Theresa. Hi. I didn't think you'd be...
- Staying? Yeah, well...

00:01:54.080 --> 00:01:56.435
- What's up?
- I thought maybe you'd need a ride...

00:01:56.600 --> 00:01:57.874
...to school.
- Oh. Thanks.

00:01:58.240 --> 00:01:59.719
Cool.

00:02:03.760 --> 00:02:07.594
Well, I can go with Marissa,
and Ryan and Theresa can go together.

00:02:07.760 --> 00:02:11.673
- No. No, Seth, really. It's okay.
- It makes more sense if you take them.

00:02:11.840 --> 00:02:15.276
Why? Because we go to the same school?
Because I live here?

00:02:17.600 --> 00:02:20.717
I'll go with Marissa,
and Ryan and Theresa can go...

00:02:20.880 --> 00:02:22.757
Yeah. Sorry. You know what?

00:02:22.920 --> 00:02:25.309
- I should have called first.
- I should've called too.

00:02:25.480 --> 00:02:28.790
- I'll just see you guys at school.
- I shouldn't just stop by. I'm gonna go.

00:02:28.960 --> 00:02:31.428
- No, wait, wait. It's...
- Call me later.

00:02:32.640 --> 00:02:33.629
We're hitchhiking.

00:03:12.200 --> 00:03:14.509
- Morning, beautiful.
- Good morning.

00:03:14.720 --> 00:03:15.994
Marissa.

00:03:16.320 --> 00:03:18.629
Kirsten. Sandy.

00:03:19.520 --> 00:03:23.752
Well, you're not gonna believe who is
<i>Riviera Magazine</i>'s Man of the Year.

00:03:23.920 --> 00:03:26.434
- Theresa.
- Mrs. Cohen. Mr. Cohen.

00:03:27.320 --> 00:03:30.869
Well, that's nice. I mean, she really
deserves the award. Good kid.

00:03:31.040 --> 00:03:32.792
It's my dad.

00:03:33.720 --> 00:03:35.995
My vote stays with Theresa.

00:03:36.720 --> 00:03:39.518
- Hi.
- Hey. Is it a good morning?

00:03:39.680 --> 00:03:42.478
So, Ryan, a couple of your friends
stopped by briefly.

00:03:42.640 --> 00:03:45.029
- Yeah, we know. It was awkward.
- Is Theresa staying?

00:03:45.200 --> 00:03:47.668
- Yeah. Looks that way.
- I thought she was going home.

00:03:47.840 --> 00:03:49.398
No. Change of plans.

00:03:49.560 --> 00:03:51.471
It's amazing. His lips don't even move.

00:03:51.840 --> 00:03:54.229
- Well, how long is she staying?
- Well...

00:03:54.800 --> 00:03:56.313
You tell them.

00:03:56.560 --> 00:04:00.872
- We're figuring it all out.
- Is she gonna, what, rent a place?

00:04:01.040 --> 00:04:03.474
What kind of lease? Month-to-month?
Year? Can she buy?

00:04:03.680 --> 00:04:05.796
- What you gonna do?
- I'm this way for a reason.

00:04:05.960 --> 00:04:09.236
- She's catering a tennis tournament.
- Is she gonna get a job after that?

00:04:09.400 --> 00:04:12.631
- What about the guy she's engaged to?
- Is she going back to school?

00:04:13.440 --> 00:04:16.113
- School. Bye.
- Now you know why I do the talking.

00:04:16.280 --> 00:04:18.794
We're gonna need a ride,
by the way. Thanks.

00:04:18.960 --> 00:04:20.996
I'll take them.
It's on my way to the office.

00:04:21.160 --> 00:04:24.436
- So is my dad gonna be in a good mood?
- Well, he should be.

00:04:24.600 --> 00:04:27.353
- He's Man of the Year.
- I meant the case.

00:04:27.520 --> 00:04:30.193
- Are you gonna take it?
- I'm thinking about it.

00:04:30.360 --> 00:04:32.874
We're gonna host the reception here
for my dad's award.

00:04:33.040 --> 00:04:35.793
And it would be nice if Uncle Shaun
could be here.

00:04:35.960 --> 00:04:38.269
Not if we have to pay for the bar tab.

00:04:38.840 --> 00:04:40.910
I'm thinking about it.

00:04:56.800 --> 00:04:58.392
Hey.

00:04:59.640 --> 00:05:01.039
Hey.

00:05:05.400 --> 00:05:07.356
Can I ask you something?

00:05:07.520 --> 00:05:09.112
Yeah. Sure.

00:05:10.680 --> 00:05:15.310
When you and I broke up,
and I started dating Ryan...

00:05:16.080 --> 00:05:19.356
...was it hard for you to see us together?
- Yeah.

00:05:20.520 --> 00:05:23.637
But, hey, we wouldn't
have broken up if I hadn't...

00:05:24.680 --> 00:05:26.636
...deserved it.
- I guess now I know...

00:05:26.800 --> 00:05:28.438
...what it feels like, huh?

00:05:28.600 --> 00:05:30.716
To deserve it.

00:05:40.200 --> 00:05:44.398
The sooner you realize that it's never
gonna go back to the way it was...

00:05:45.120 --> 00:05:47.680
...the sooner you can move on.

00:05:51.680 --> 00:05:53.716
Okay. I'll see you guys later.

00:05:53.880 --> 00:05:57.668
- Hey, Ryan. I'm sorry about this morning.
- No, no. That's okay.

00:05:57.840 --> 00:06:02.470
- I didn't realize she was gonna be there.
- Yeah. There was a change of plans.

00:06:02.640 --> 00:06:04.039
How long is she staying for?

00:06:04.200 --> 00:06:07.078
No, she's gotta find a job, a place to live.

00:06:07.240 --> 00:06:09.879
- Minor details, huh?
- Yeah.

00:06:11.120 --> 00:06:13.509
Well, if you need any help...

00:06:13.720 --> 00:06:15.392
Thanks.

00:06:18.120 --> 00:06:20.714
- Check out Gramps. He looks angry.
- That's because he is.

00:06:20.880 --> 00:06:22.393
Why? He's on a magazine cover.

00:06:22.560 --> 00:06:24.869
Hard to believe that doesn't
leave him fulfilled.

00:06:25.040 --> 00:06:28.032
Totally. I know. I love the society page.

00:06:28.200 --> 00:06:30.919
It's like, suddenly, all of the people
we know are famous.

00:06:31.080 --> 00:06:33.833
- Diana Kahn totally got a chin implant.
- They have chin implants?

00:06:34.000 --> 00:06:36.389
My dad does them.
He says chins are the new nose.

00:06:36.720 --> 00:06:40.315
- So did Picasso.
- Really? What hospital does he work for?

00:06:42.240 --> 00:06:44.196
Kidding. I'm not that dumb. Just shallow.

00:06:44.720 --> 00:06:47.757
Is all this talk of Newport and
plastic surgery boring you, Anna?

00:06:47.920 --> 00:06:50.115
No. Actually, I'm savoring it.

00:06:50.280 --> 00:06:53.750
I won't be hearing it much longer.
I'm leaving.

00:06:53.920 --> 00:06:57.435
- You getting dessert?
- No. I'm going back to Pittsburgh.

00:06:57.600 --> 00:06:58.828
- What?
- I'm gonna go live...

00:06:59.000 --> 00:07:02.356
...with my aunt and uncle.
I've just kind of had enough of Newport...

00:07:02.520 --> 00:07:04.476
...so I'm leaving.

00:07:08.760 --> 00:07:12.355
Park-ranger cadet?
Full-time position available.

00:07:12.720 --> 00:07:14.551
I wouldn't look good in the hat.

00:07:14.720 --> 00:07:17.154
You'd get to put out forest fires.

00:07:17.320 --> 00:07:19.675
Moving on.

00:07:21.200 --> 00:07:23.475
Classifieds are...

00:07:23.640 --> 00:07:25.710
Depressing?

00:07:26.800 --> 00:07:30.156
- We'll find something. We'll figure it out.
- I know.

00:07:31.160 --> 00:07:33.754
I'm glad you called me to come meet you.

00:07:34.240 --> 00:07:38.199
Who knew being unemployed
could be so much fun?

00:07:43.360 --> 00:07:45.316
I gotta get to class.

00:07:57.040 --> 00:07:59.679
- It will be okay.
- Okay.

00:08:15.440 --> 00:08:16.953
Kaitlin. Hi.

00:08:17.120 --> 00:08:19.156
Hi, Luke. What's going on?

00:08:19.320 --> 00:08:23.154
Well, I just finished school for the day,
you know, which is always a good thing.

00:08:23.320 --> 00:08:25.959
I so know what you mean.

00:08:27.360 --> 00:08:30.397
- Luke. What are you doing here?
- We're talking, Mom.

00:08:31.000 --> 00:08:33.514
Go get ready.
Daddy's coming to take you to dinner.

00:08:33.720 --> 00:08:36.234
So I'll see you soon?

00:08:41.160 --> 00:08:42.957
Luke, you know not to
come to the house.

00:08:43.120 --> 00:08:45.236
- We meet at the motel.
- I just thought...

00:08:45.400 --> 00:08:47.356
...that you needed help
with your DSL.

00:08:47.520 --> 00:08:50.478
Luke, as much as I want
high-speed Internet access...

00:08:50.640 --> 00:08:53.712
...it's not worth Kaitlin
becoming suspicious.

00:08:56.600 --> 00:08:58.909
Hey, Jules. Luke.

00:08:59.080 --> 00:09:01.833
Luke just came by
to defrag my hard drive.

00:09:02.920 --> 00:09:04.399
Okay.

00:09:04.560 --> 00:09:06.755
Hurry along, Luke. Make it quick.

00:09:11.520 --> 00:09:13.715
I'll make sure Kaitlin's ready.

00:09:18.280 --> 00:09:22.592
Hey, should I put another piece of
swordfish on for Theresa? Or Marissa?

00:09:22.880 --> 00:09:24.950
Or any other ladies you plan
on having over?

00:09:25.120 --> 00:09:29.352
- I was gonna go pick up Theresa, so...
- Done and done.

00:09:29.520 --> 00:09:32.080
So how's that going with you guys?

00:09:32.800 --> 00:09:34.916
Good. Just trying to figure it out.

00:09:35.080 --> 00:09:38.117
- "It" being?
- Pretty much everything.

00:09:38.280 --> 00:09:41.272
- You want to know what I think?
- You're gonna tell me either way.

00:09:41.440 --> 00:09:44.796
Like my own son.
You're in high school, she should be...

00:09:44.960 --> 00:09:48.669
...you're both in way over your heads.
She's got no real job, no place to live.

00:09:48.840 --> 00:09:50.910
- Don't ask if she can stay here.
- I wouldn't.

00:09:51.080 --> 00:09:54.436
Good. You have no idea what Kirsten did
the last time I floated such a concept.

00:09:54.600 --> 00:09:57.239
Theresa's got family in Chino.
She's got a life in Chino.

00:09:57.400 --> 00:09:59.914
Running away is not the answer.

00:10:00.280 --> 00:10:01.508
I know.

00:10:01.680 --> 00:10:04.319
- It's kind of crazy.
- No. It's sweet.

00:10:04.480 --> 00:10:08.678
It's totally misguided,
but it's kind of charming.

00:10:08.840 --> 00:10:14.358
You gotta tell her. It's time she faced
the music. Or at least the fianc��.

00:10:14.600 --> 00:10:18.195
And you're gonna do that thing with
the white lights in your back yard, right?

00:10:18.360 --> 00:10:22.273
- Of course, Dad.
- Good. I love the white lights.

00:10:22.440 --> 00:10:25.671
- And no cilantro. I hate cilantro.
- You're Man of the Year.

00:10:25.840 --> 00:10:28.354
I think they can make some food
without cilantro.

00:10:28.560 --> 00:10:30.118
I'll have to make a toast.

00:10:30.280 --> 00:10:32.510
You've got that '73 Dom
in your wine cellar, yes?

00:10:32.680 --> 00:10:34.830
I think you went through that
on your birthday.

00:10:35.280 --> 00:10:39.398
- Kirsten. Mr. Nichol.
- Why don't you call him Caleb.

00:10:43.000 --> 00:10:44.797
- Congrats on your award.
- Means nothing.

00:10:44.960 --> 00:10:47.349
They're lucky I agreed to pose
for their front cover.

00:10:47.520 --> 00:10:50.398
Use that in your speech.
Want me to set a place for Theresa?

00:10:50.560 --> 00:10:53.791
- I'll get back to you on that one.
- I'm gonna go check on the Dom.

00:10:53.960 --> 00:10:58.158
- I was thinking chardonnay for dinner.
- No, get the pinot.

00:10:58.920 --> 00:11:01.639
Do what you like. It's your house.
I'm just making a salad.

00:11:01.800 --> 00:11:04.598
Man of the Year and still so modest.

00:11:04.760 --> 00:11:07.718
I'm so glad to see it
hasn't gone to your head, Cal.

00:11:07.880 --> 00:11:10.269
The case. Have you made your decision?

00:11:10.440 --> 00:11:15.275
I've decided what it'll take to make me
decide. You tell Kirsten everything.

00:11:15.800 --> 00:11:18.917
- She's better off not knowing.
- She's not. You are.

00:11:19.480 --> 00:11:22.040
She is already implicated,
without her knowledge.

00:11:22.200 --> 00:11:23.872
Then why worry her?

00:11:24.040 --> 00:11:26.918
- This may all go away, you know.
- It may not.

00:11:27.080 --> 00:11:28.911
I won't spend the next year
lying to her.

00:11:29.080 --> 00:11:31.753
So if you want my help,
you tell her everything.

00:11:39.960 --> 00:11:41.712
- Hi.
- Hey.

00:11:41.880 --> 00:11:44.348
- We should talk.
- I have news.

00:11:45.800 --> 00:11:47.313
You go first.

00:11:47.560 --> 00:11:49.312
I just got off the phone with Eddie.

00:11:49.680 --> 00:11:53.036
And I told him I'm not coming home
anytime soon.

00:11:53.560 --> 00:11:55.869
- You did?
- He didn't take it well.

00:11:56.040 --> 00:11:58.679
But now that I did it,
which I can't believe I did...

00:11:58.840 --> 00:12:02.799
...I feel so much more free or something.

00:12:03.520 --> 00:12:05.829
What did you want to talk about?

00:12:08.280 --> 00:12:10.350
How do you feel about swordfish?

00:12:19.120 --> 00:12:22.237
- So she's leaving.
- No, she's staying.

00:12:22.400 --> 00:12:23.753
What? When did you
talk to Anna?

00:12:23.920 --> 00:12:25.831
She told me she's going
back to Pittsburgh.

00:12:26.000 --> 00:12:30.471
- Anna's going back to Pittsburgh?
- Not anymore, according to you.

00:12:30.920 --> 00:12:34.037
- I'm totally confused.
- She, Anna, is leaving.

00:12:34.200 --> 00:12:36.191
She, Theresa, is staying.

00:12:36.360 --> 00:12:38.112
Right. Got it.

00:12:39.360 --> 00:12:42.909
- So she really is leaving.
- That sucks.

00:12:43.520 --> 00:12:46.193
Do you think it's because of me?

00:12:47.840 --> 00:12:50.195
I can't believe I caused a girl
to leave the state.

00:12:50.360 --> 00:12:53.557
- The county, maybe. Sure. Fine.
- You really think it's because of you?

00:12:53.920 --> 00:12:57.390
Well, I mean, we broke up, she went
back East, she had a great time...

00:12:57.560 --> 00:12:59.312
...she comes back, only to see me...

00:12:59.480 --> 00:13:02.119
...standing on a coffee cart
declaring my love for Summer.

00:13:02.320 --> 00:13:04.675
Maybe she just doesn't feel
that comfortable here.

00:13:04.840 --> 00:13:08.355
I know. I get that. But if it is because
of me, maybe I can talk her out of it.

00:13:08.520 --> 00:13:10.476
Except I can't ask her
if it's because of me...

00:13:10.640 --> 00:13:12.437
...without sounding totally
self-absorbed.

00:13:12.600 --> 00:13:15.398
And I'm not self-absorbed, right, Ryan?
Me. Me.

00:13:15.560 --> 00:13:19.439
- Me.
- Sorry. Just thinking about Theresa.

00:13:20.640 --> 00:13:24.076
- She's staying. What am I gonna do?
- She's leaving. What am I gonna do?

00:13:30.920 --> 00:13:33.309
Kiki, thanks for meeting me.

00:13:33.480 --> 00:13:36.517
- Is everything okay?
- Why don't you have a seat.

00:13:42.440 --> 00:13:44.715
Is it Uncle Shaun?

00:13:46.440 --> 00:13:51.036
The hotel room that he accidentally
stumbled into the other day...

00:13:51.200 --> 00:13:53.953
- Joel McKuin was staying there.
- That's quite a coincidence.

00:13:54.120 --> 00:13:57.396
Joel McKuin is the leading lumber
supplier on the West Coast.

00:13:57.840 --> 00:14:00.274
Not such a coincidence.

00:14:00.600 --> 00:14:04.309
It's not the first time that he's
accidentally stumbled into a hotel room.

00:14:04.480 --> 00:14:06.391
It's just the first time he's got caught.

00:14:06.560 --> 00:14:08.471
I knew Uncle Shaun
was a tough negotiator.

00:14:08.640 --> 00:14:11.916
And, yeah, he sent extra-nice
Christmas presents to certain Teamsters.

00:14:12.080 --> 00:14:15.390
Breaking and entering? Theft? What else?

00:14:15.560 --> 00:14:18.597
Blackmail? Racketeering?

00:14:20.880 --> 00:14:23.075
- Is he going to jail?
- Not if Sandy can help it.

00:14:23.240 --> 00:14:26.630
Well, if he can't,
are they gonna go after you?

00:14:27.640 --> 00:14:30.108
I'm afraid it's not just me.

00:14:39.480 --> 00:14:40.913
Hey.

00:14:41.320 --> 00:14:44.437
- Catching up on Western civ?
- Yeah, Spanish Inquisition. Lot of fun.

00:14:44.600 --> 00:14:47.717
Tell me about it.
Could they give us any more reading?

00:14:47.920 --> 00:14:49.717
- Get up.
- Eddie. Eddie, what's going on?

00:14:49.880 --> 00:14:52.348
You know exactly what's going on.

00:14:53.000 --> 00:14:55.230
- You sleep with her?
- No. No.

00:14:55.400 --> 00:14:57.868
No? Then why'd she call me
and say she's not coming back?

00:14:58.040 --> 00:15:00.349
- Why would she stay here?
- This isn't the right time.

00:15:00.520 --> 00:15:02.988
No, don't touch me.
After all I did for you growing up.

00:15:03.160 --> 00:15:04.639
The least you can do is
be honest with me.

00:15:04.800 --> 00:15:06.756
Now, you be a man, and you tell me.

00:15:06.920 --> 00:15:08.672
- Are you sleeping with her?
- No.

00:15:08.840 --> 00:15:13.277
Excuse me. This lounge is
for faculty and students only.

00:15:16.800 --> 00:15:18.950
I'm not letting her go.

00:15:33.120 --> 00:15:35.918
Anna. Hey.

00:15:36.080 --> 00:15:37.877
- Hi.
- This is nice weather we're having.

00:15:38.040 --> 00:15:40.156
- Yeah.
- Yeah. Oh, did you hear? The Lakers won.

00:15:40.320 --> 00:15:42.436
- Oh, did they?
- Yeah. Yeah, they did.

00:15:42.600 --> 00:15:45.637
There's something else I wanted
to talk to you about. What was it?

00:15:45.800 --> 00:15:47.791
That's it. You're leaving.

00:15:47.960 --> 00:15:50.758
- Why the hell are you leaving?
- You know, I'm late for class.

00:15:50.920 --> 00:15:53.434
- You got at least three minutes.
- It's too complicated.

00:15:53.600 --> 00:15:56.160
Why don't you start with one reason.
There's gotta be...

00:15:56.320 --> 00:15:59.471
...one main, overriding reason.
- Fine. Look, I miss the seasons.

00:15:59.640 --> 00:16:03.633
I miss fall foliage. I miss the snow.
I miss the first signs of spring.

00:16:03.800 --> 00:16:06.394
- You miss the seasons?
- Yeah, and...

00:16:07.160 --> 00:16:08.513
And?

00:16:08.680 --> 00:16:11.513
And my little dog, Swifty.
We left him with my aunt and uncle.

00:16:11.680 --> 00:16:15.639
And the Jimmy Stewart Museum.
And Peanut Butter Cup Pie at Dingbats.

00:16:15.800 --> 00:16:21.591
The vinyl selection at Record Village.
And Sundays, the SuperFlea Fleamarket.

00:16:21.960 --> 00:16:24.428
I guess I did get it
into three minutes, huh?

00:16:24.600 --> 00:16:28.673
So that's it? There's not, like,
one other reason?

00:16:28.840 --> 00:16:31.718
- Did I say Peanut Butter Cup Pies?
- Yeah.

00:16:32.040 --> 00:16:34.952
- Then, no.
- Good. Excellent.

00:16:36.800 --> 00:16:39.155
Tomorrow, we're having this thing
for my grandpa...

00:16:39.320 --> 00:16:41.356
- I leave tomorrow.
- Not without saying goodbye.

00:16:41.520 --> 00:16:43.112
- I'll come say goodbye.
- Okay.

00:16:52.600 --> 00:16:54.158
Is there anything I can do to help?

00:16:54.320 --> 00:16:55.594
- You, Theresa...?
- Yeah, sure.

00:16:55.760 --> 00:16:58.228
She needs a job and a place to live,
if you got anything.

00:16:58.400 --> 00:17:00.789
Does she need a friend?
I could help out there.

00:17:00.960 --> 00:17:03.394
Invite her to Caleb's party.
We'll all hang out.

00:17:03.720 --> 00:17:06.393
Why the hell would you want that?

00:17:08.680 --> 00:17:11.240
Look, I'm used to getting what I want.

00:17:11.400 --> 00:17:14.073
Which I know is not
the most attractive quality.

00:17:14.240 --> 00:17:16.310
But I also know I can't compete
with a girl...

00:17:16.480 --> 00:17:18.516
...you've known your whole life.

00:17:19.840 --> 00:17:22.832
Not after everything that's
just come between us.

00:17:25.320 --> 00:17:29.916
I don't think she has clothes,
a dress, for it.

00:17:32.800 --> 00:17:34.870
But thanks.

00:17:49.040 --> 00:17:50.519
Hey.

00:17:51.600 --> 00:17:54.831
- How was the rest of your day?
- I wanted to see how you were doing.

00:17:55.040 --> 00:17:57.952
After the Heights,
I knew that my dad wasn't aboveboard.

00:17:58.120 --> 00:18:01.590
But this is beyond anything
that I could have imagined.

00:18:01.760 --> 00:18:03.079
We're gonna figure this out.

00:18:03.280 --> 00:18:05.635
You better believe I'll do
all I can to protect you.

00:18:05.800 --> 00:18:09.315
No. I don't want you to.
I'm going to get outside counsel.

00:18:09.560 --> 00:18:12.074
I do not want you involved.

00:18:12.840 --> 00:18:16.594
When I asked for your help,
I had no idea what I was asking you for.

00:18:16.760 --> 00:18:19.718
- I know that.
- But this is my mistake, not yours.

00:18:19.880 --> 00:18:25.000
And I will not let you compromise
yourself, not even for me.

00:18:25.160 --> 00:18:26.957
I'm gonna call the caterers.

00:18:27.120 --> 00:18:31.033
Make sure that there's no cilantro
for the Man of the Year.

00:18:42.880 --> 00:18:44.836
She's lying. I know it.

00:18:45.000 --> 00:18:48.709
- What? Who?
- Anna.

00:18:48.880 --> 00:18:52.668
- You're thinking about Anna right now?
- I just...

00:18:52.840 --> 00:18:56.071
I just wish I could convince her
not to leave because of me.

00:18:56.240 --> 00:18:59.198
You think she's leaving
just because of you?

00:18:59.360 --> 00:19:01.157
It makes sense, doesn't it?

00:19:01.320 --> 00:19:03.595
Yeah. But even if I thought it,
I wouldn't say it.

00:19:04.000 --> 00:19:07.390
I mean, it's a little self-absorbed, Cohen.

00:19:09.160 --> 00:19:12.835
- I just never wanted to hurt her feelings.
- Maybe she just doesn't like it here.

00:19:13.000 --> 00:19:15.389
I hear there are a few people who don't.

00:19:15.560 --> 00:19:18.836
It does rain sometimes in January.

00:19:25.760 --> 00:19:27.671
I'm kind of...

00:19:28.360 --> 00:19:30.828
I'm kind of hungry. You want to eat?

00:19:31.440 --> 00:19:32.953
Thanks.

00:19:40.880 --> 00:19:42.472
- Hi.
- Hey.

00:19:42.640 --> 00:19:45.359
Are you still good at foot massages?
I've been on my feet...

00:19:45.520 --> 00:19:48.671
- We gotta talk.
- So no foot massage?

00:19:48.840 --> 00:19:52.150
Listen. Listen, I don't know
what to do about us.

00:19:52.320 --> 00:19:55.596
I can't get you a job, a place to live.

00:19:55.760 --> 00:19:57.318
- I live in a pool house.
- Shut up.

00:19:57.480 --> 00:20:00.790
Shut the hell up.
I don't need you to take care of me.

00:20:00.960 --> 00:20:02.951
- I can take care of myself.
- I know, I know.

00:20:03.120 --> 00:20:07.591
I am not one of these Newport chicks
that needs a trust fund to survive.

00:20:07.760 --> 00:20:12.550
But the fact that you thought
I needed you is really great.

00:20:12.880 --> 00:20:14.677
Sweet.

00:20:15.440 --> 00:20:17.112
Sexy.

00:20:21.360 --> 00:20:23.430
What about Eddie?

00:20:24.200 --> 00:20:27.397
I told Eddie that I can't
marry him right now.

00:20:27.560 --> 00:20:29.471
Just because you're okay with it
doesn't mean he is.

00:20:29.640 --> 00:20:32.712
I'm not okay with it,
I just know it's for the best.

00:20:33.320 --> 00:20:35.515
I'm here to be with you.

00:20:42.960 --> 00:20:44.439
Are we doing this?

00:20:44.640 --> 00:20:47.757
It's not like we haven't before.

00:21:47.920 --> 00:21:50.309
- What's the matter?
- It's not like home.

00:21:50.480 --> 00:21:53.153
I got people that notice
if I don't get back.

00:21:53.320 --> 00:21:56.756
I had the day off. If you want to go
to the beach or to the pier tonight...

00:21:57.280 --> 00:21:59.032
- Actually, I have a thing.
- A thing?

00:21:59.200 --> 00:22:01.395
Kirsten's dad is being honored
by some magazine.

00:22:01.560 --> 00:22:04.632
They're having a cocktail party
at the Cohen house.

00:22:05.920 --> 00:22:07.399
You...

00:22:07.560 --> 00:22:09.198
You want to come?

00:22:11.040 --> 00:22:12.155
Do you want me to come?

00:22:12.320 --> 00:22:15.949
- I'm kind of getting the vibe that...
- No. Yeah. No.

00:22:16.120 --> 00:22:18.998
It's just, you know what these things
are like, these people...

00:22:19.160 --> 00:22:20.798
And it might be kind of weird.

00:22:20.960 --> 00:22:24.316
The girl who serves food at the party
is now a guest at the party.

00:22:24.480 --> 00:22:25.799
I wasn't saying that.

00:22:25.960 --> 00:22:30.909
- I feel like you're not trying to invite me.
- No, I do. I am.

00:22:31.080 --> 00:22:33.116
I didn't think you'd want to go.

00:22:33.280 --> 00:22:35.157
I don't want to go.

00:22:35.320 --> 00:22:38.312
I want to make sure you're not
embarrassed to bring me to things.

00:22:38.480 --> 00:22:39.879
I'm not.

00:22:40.040 --> 00:22:43.589
Good. I have nothing to wear anyway.

00:22:44.520 --> 00:22:48.513
But come over after,
and we can both wear nothing.

00:22:58.040 --> 00:23:01.635
Well, if you keep looking up like that,
all you're gonna see is a bad shot.

00:23:01.800 --> 00:23:04.394
Hey, Hodes. How are things
at the DA's office?

00:23:04.560 --> 00:23:09.156
Better since you left the PD's office.
My people seem to win a few more.

00:23:09.360 --> 00:23:13.592
That's why I left.
I started feeling bad for you.

00:23:13.760 --> 00:23:17.116
So why don't I think it's a
wild coincidence to see you here?

00:23:17.320 --> 00:23:20.630
You have trust issues.
That's why you've never been married.

00:23:20.800 --> 00:23:25.191
Well, saves me a phone call.
We have a deal to offer your client.

00:23:25.360 --> 00:23:26.713
Client?

00:23:26.880 --> 00:23:28.313
Shaughnessy.

00:23:28.480 --> 00:23:31.358
- He's not my client.
- That's not what he said.

00:23:31.520 --> 00:23:35.433
He's drunk most of the time. You can't
take anything he says very seriously.

00:23:35.600 --> 00:23:38.990
We're taking what we think
he has to say very seriously.

00:23:40.160 --> 00:23:42.435
Just out of curiosity...

00:23:43.680 --> 00:23:45.750
...what kind of deal
were you gonna offer him?

00:23:45.920 --> 00:23:49.230
- Curiosity?
- Yeah, mild.

00:23:49.440 --> 00:23:54.150
Okay, if he were to cooperate, let us
know who signs his marching orders...

00:23:54.320 --> 00:23:56.231
...we'd plead him down
to a lesser charge.

00:23:56.400 --> 00:23:59.710
Unless the plaintiff decides
to drop the charges.

00:23:59.880 --> 00:24:01.677
Then he would have no reason to talk.

00:24:01.840 --> 00:24:05.116
Except the plaintiff has no reason
to do that. Right?

00:24:06.960 --> 00:24:11.988
Let me tell you something, Sandy. The
Newport Group is Orange County's Enron.

00:24:12.160 --> 00:24:14.276
You make this just a little
difficult for me...

00:24:14.440 --> 00:24:16.510
...and I'll come down on you
as hard as I can.

00:24:16.680 --> 00:24:19.069
- This must be a reelection year.
- Oh, spare me.

00:24:19.520 --> 00:24:23.115
You and I have been friends for years.
That's why Caleb Nichol hired you.

00:24:23.280 --> 00:24:26.636
It used to be, Sandy Cohen's moral
compass wouldn't point him anywhere...

00:24:26.800 --> 00:24:29.792
...except the direction of truth.
No matter who he took down.

00:24:29.960 --> 00:24:32.713
Spoken like a man
who's never been married.

00:24:33.000 --> 00:24:35.719
I just can't hit it any better than that.

00:24:37.160 --> 00:24:39.230
Good to see you again.

00:24:45.200 --> 00:24:46.997
- Hey, man, where you been?
- Theresa's.

00:24:47.160 --> 00:24:49.390
- Your parents say anything?
- No, I covered for you.

00:24:49.560 --> 00:24:52.233
You shouldn't do this.
You're sleeping there? That's serious.

00:24:52.400 --> 00:24:54.595
- I fell asleep.
- I heard about some scary guy...

00:24:54.760 --> 00:24:56.796
...that showed up at school.
Was it Eddie?

00:24:56.960 --> 00:24:58.234
- He came to talk.
- Yeah?

00:24:58.400 --> 00:25:00.914
About how it's getting serious
between you and Theresa?

00:25:01.080 --> 00:25:03.878
- You and Anna? You talk?
- Do not change the subject to me.

00:25:04.040 --> 00:25:06.110
I'm powerless not to talk
about it. I tried.

00:25:06.280 --> 00:25:08.350
She had a list of reasons
why she's leaving.

00:25:08.520 --> 00:25:10.158
- Didn't make the cut?
- She's lying.

00:25:10.320 --> 00:25:12.880
I want her to know that I'm sorry
I hurt her feelings.

00:25:13.040 --> 00:25:15.873
But she doesn't have to do this.
She shouldn't be doing this.

00:25:16.040 --> 00:25:19.237
- Then just tell her.
- Just tell her, huh?

00:25:19.400 --> 00:25:21.675
Simple. Honest.
No wonder I never considered it.

00:25:21.840 --> 00:25:25.355
Okay, fine. I'll tell her tonight.
Might have to have a little bubbly first.

00:25:25.520 --> 00:25:26.509
A little <i>veritas in vino</i>,
know what I mean?

00:25:26.680 --> 00:25:28.238
Hardly ever.

00:25:29.440 --> 00:25:31.078
Coming.

00:25:35.840 --> 00:25:38.434
Hey. Come in.

00:25:39.240 --> 00:25:42.755
- How are you?
- Good. What's going on?

00:25:42.920 --> 00:25:45.639
- Well, there's this party tonight, and...
- I heard.

00:25:46.160 --> 00:25:49.072
Yeah, well, I thought
maybe you'd want to go.

00:25:49.240 --> 00:25:52.357
I can't. I didn't really bring
any of my nice clothes with me.

00:25:52.840 --> 00:25:55.559
Well, I have some options.

00:26:06.560 --> 00:26:11.350
Hello? Hello? Hey, Joel.
Thanks for getting back to me.

00:26:12.080 --> 00:26:14.071
No, actually, now's a perfect time.

00:26:14.280 --> 00:26:18.432
- Come on. Smile for your father, Kiki.
- I'm smiling on the inside.

00:26:18.680 --> 00:26:20.113
<i>Veritas in vino.</i>

00:26:20.320 --> 00:26:22.197
Yeah. Then we have a deal?

00:26:22.360 --> 00:26:24.715
Why spend a lot of money when
you can make a lot?

00:26:24.880 --> 00:26:26.791
Yeah. Caleb'll be pleased.

00:26:26.960 --> 00:26:30.873
Yes, Mr. McKuin, I'm fully aware.
We do what we must.

00:26:37.440 --> 00:26:38.998
Theresa coming?

00:26:39.160 --> 00:26:41.037
Nope. Marissa?

00:26:41.200 --> 00:26:43.031
I doubt it.

00:26:44.360 --> 00:26:50.037
Look, I get why you're doing what
you're doing, but she does really love you.

00:26:50.240 --> 00:26:54.472
- I know. It's just...
- Yeah. The Oliver thing. I know.

00:26:54.640 --> 00:26:56.073
It was messed up.

00:26:56.240 --> 00:27:01.155
But, hey, she dated Luke for years.
You can't always trust her judgment.

00:27:02.120 --> 00:27:04.793
But she has a good heart.

00:27:11.280 --> 00:27:13.748
Not your typical back-yard barbecue.

00:27:14.000 --> 00:27:16.639
Yeah, well, they never are.

00:27:19.320 --> 00:27:20.753
You...

00:27:22.240 --> 00:27:23.958
I had some help.

00:27:27.600 --> 00:27:29.033
Coop.

00:27:30.000 --> 00:27:33.754
- That's a nice one, sir.
- Right here, please. Eyes right here.

00:27:33.920 --> 00:27:38.835
Come on, Seth. Get in the picture.
You are the future of the company.

00:27:39.000 --> 00:27:40.956
There's something to look forward to.

00:27:41.120 --> 00:27:44.032
You'll grow out of comic books
and grow into wanting to be rich.

00:27:44.240 --> 00:27:45.275
No, I won't.

00:27:50.840 --> 00:27:52.353
- Hey.
- Hi.

00:27:53.000 --> 00:27:55.673
I just came to say goodbye.
My plane's leaving soon.

00:27:55.840 --> 00:27:57.956
- You're really leaving.
- Yeah.

00:27:58.400 --> 00:28:02.234
Well, you might not believe this,
but I'm gonna miss you.

00:28:02.400 --> 00:28:04.595
What's more unbelievable
is that I'm gonna miss you.

00:28:04.760 --> 00:28:06.398
Pretty unbelievable.

00:28:06.560 --> 00:28:09.870
- Bye, Blanche.
- See you, Rose.

00:28:11.840 --> 00:28:15.799
Have you seen Molly Miller's boob job?
They're huge.

00:28:15.960 --> 00:28:18.758
Lois Robin's face-lift?

00:28:18.920 --> 00:28:22.390
Diane Kahn totally had chin implants.

00:28:22.560 --> 00:28:23.879
They have chin implants?

00:28:24.040 --> 00:28:26.554
Oh, yeah. Chins are the new nose.
Haven't you heard?

00:28:26.720 --> 00:28:30.110
- Hey, Anna. Theresa.
- Nice to meet you.

00:28:32.760 --> 00:28:34.955
Came to say goodbye to Seth?

00:28:35.440 --> 00:28:37.237
Yeah.

00:28:37.720 --> 00:28:40.029
Could you give him this?

00:28:41.880 --> 00:28:44.269
It's supposed to say everything
that I couldn't say.

00:28:44.440 --> 00:28:45.839
But now that I'm here,
I just...

00:28:46.000 --> 00:28:48.514
...can't say anything at all.
- Yeah. Yeah. Of course.

00:28:49.040 --> 00:28:51.270
See you, Ryan.

00:28:52.560 --> 00:28:54.835
Thanks for teaching me how to waltz.

00:28:55.000 --> 00:28:58.993
Have the best life. You deserve it.

00:29:00.880 --> 00:29:02.279
- Bye.
- Bye.

00:29:13.640 --> 00:29:16.154
You look so hot.

00:29:16.560 --> 00:29:18.710
Not here, Luke. Behave.

00:29:18.880 --> 00:29:21.440
I know. It's just...

00:29:23.200 --> 00:29:24.872
...your ass.

00:29:33.720 --> 00:29:37.554
We do all right.
Excuse me, guys. Thanks.

00:29:40.880 --> 00:29:44.190
I saw the DA today.
It didn't go what I would call "well."

00:29:44.360 --> 00:29:47.079
I thought he was your friend.
You made deals all the time.

00:29:47.240 --> 00:29:50.710
It's an election year. It seems you're
not too popular with the people.

00:29:50.880 --> 00:29:53.155
That the best you could do?
I need to make my toast.

00:29:53.320 --> 00:29:55.993
I'll make this go away,
but you'll have to give something up.

00:29:56.160 --> 00:30:00.711
Joel McKuin needs to be the chief supplier
for the next big Newport Group contract.

00:30:00.880 --> 00:30:04.156
You won't be buying wholesale,
but it'll work.

00:30:05.600 --> 00:30:09.388
- I knew I could rely on you.
- Not if you were Man of the Century.

00:30:09.560 --> 00:30:13.109
What's the matter, Sandy?
You cut deals for your clients all the time.

00:30:13.320 --> 00:30:17.757
Yeah, well, usually, they're the ones
that have broken the law, not me.

00:30:20.920 --> 00:30:24.515
Mr. Nichol, it's time for your speech.
Right this way.

00:30:30.720 --> 00:30:32.278
Ladies and gentlemen,
it is my pleasure...

00:30:32.440 --> 00:30:35.159
- Hey, Jules.
- James.

00:30:35.320 --> 00:30:38.790
Now, forgive me, this can't
possibly be happening, right?

00:30:38.960 --> 00:30:43.636
- I'm crazy to even think it, right?
- Think what?

00:30:43.800 --> 00:30:48.476
Okay, that's what I thought.
Because it would destroy Marissa.

00:30:50.280 --> 00:30:51.793
We know she's been through enough.

00:30:51.960 --> 00:30:55.475
Honestly, Jimmy, I don't know
what you're talking about.

00:30:55.640 --> 00:30:59.394
- Now, Caleb's speaking.
- It really is a tremendous honor.

00:30:59.560 --> 00:31:01.471
Few publications better represent...

00:31:01.640 --> 00:31:05.519
...this great county of ours
than <i>Riviera Magazine.</i>

00:31:16.320 --> 00:31:18.675
I'll be right back.
I'm gonna give Seth his letter.

00:31:18.840 --> 00:31:21.877
Okay. I'll be here,
trying to spot the chin implants.

00:31:22.920 --> 00:31:25.480
My story has its own cast of characters.

00:31:25.640 --> 00:31:29.553
One doesn't become <i>Riviera</i> Man
of the Year without some help.

00:31:29.720 --> 00:31:31.950
Where would I be without
my wonderful family?

00:31:32.120 --> 00:31:34.350
My beautiful daughter Kirsten,
and my favorite...

00:31:34.520 --> 00:31:38.798
Well, my only grandson, Seth.
Come join me.

00:31:40.800 --> 00:31:43.872
- What are you doing here?
- I just want to talk. Can't you listen?

00:31:46.800 --> 00:31:49.837
- Let's go somewhere and figure this out.
- I'm not going anywhere.

00:31:51.520 --> 00:31:54.910
Stay the hell away from me. You're lucky
I don't kick your ass right here.

00:31:55.080 --> 00:31:57.196
- Look, can we please just go?
- Let go!

00:32:05.040 --> 00:32:06.951
What the hell is going on?

00:32:14.880 --> 00:32:16.916
Why don't you leave
before the cops get here.

00:32:17.080 --> 00:32:18.513
- You're dead!
- Right now.

00:32:18.680 --> 00:32:22.468
Don't ever come home. You're dead.
You hear me? Get off me, man.

00:32:33.520 --> 00:32:37.354
Oh, that's gonna be quite a shiner.
But, hey, they look good on you.

00:32:37.520 --> 00:32:38.669
Yeah? Thanks.

00:32:38.840 --> 00:32:41.479
I'm so sorry. About everything.

00:32:41.640 --> 00:32:43.756
Oh, it's okay, sweetie. It's not your fault.

00:32:43.920 --> 00:32:48.391
Hey, I heard there was a rumble in the
bedroom. I'm gonna go break it up.

00:32:51.680 --> 00:32:53.193
You okay?

00:32:54.200 --> 00:32:57.158
- I can't believe Anna didn't show.
- Actually...

00:32:59.960 --> 00:33:02.679
- You're just giving me this now?
- I was a little distracted.

00:33:03.800 --> 00:33:06.553
The ink's all smudged.
I can't even read it.

00:33:09.720 --> 00:33:11.438
Is that a V or a Q?

00:33:12.600 --> 00:33:14.318
Okay, here, look. Right there.

00:33:14.480 --> 00:33:17.790
That says, "I love you." Then what
is that word? "Azerbaijan"? "Aztecs"?

00:33:17.960 --> 00:33:19.439
- Aspirin.
- It says "aspirin"?

00:33:19.600 --> 00:33:22.478
- You're giving me a headache.
- "Confucius"? What's this C-word?

00:33:22.640 --> 00:33:23.789
- Confusing?
- "Confusing"?

00:33:23.960 --> 00:33:26.952
No. You're confusing me.
What do you care what it says?

00:33:27.120 --> 00:33:29.839
Anna couldn't even say goodbye.
She's leaving because of me.

00:33:30.000 --> 00:33:32.070
- I don't want it to happen.
- What is going on?

00:33:32.280 --> 00:33:35.556
Last week, you're on a coffee cart
declaring your eternal love for me.

00:33:35.720 --> 00:33:38.678
Now you're all like,
"Anna's letter. I can't read it."

00:33:38.840 --> 00:33:43.231
This isn't like that, okay? She's just my
friend, and I don't want her to leave.

00:33:45.600 --> 00:33:47.352
Then go.

00:33:47.520 --> 00:33:49.397
Stop her.

00:33:53.680 --> 00:33:56.274
- So, what are you gonna do?
- I need to call Eddie.

00:33:56.440 --> 00:33:59.000
Try and straighten everything out.

00:33:59.160 --> 00:34:00.991
It's gonna be okay.

00:34:01.680 --> 00:34:05.389
I'm sorry to interrupt. I need you to drive
me to the airport. I gotta stop Anna.

00:34:05.560 --> 00:34:08.677
- You can't drive yourself?
- I've had three glasses of champagne.

00:34:08.840 --> 00:34:11.115
You know how it goes
straight to my head. Please.

00:34:11.280 --> 00:34:13.714
- You should go. He needs you.
- Thank you very much.

00:34:17.600 --> 00:34:20.273
You're gonna be at the motel
when I get back?

00:34:20.440 --> 00:34:22.510
I don't want you to be late.

00:34:31.960 --> 00:34:34.315
Hey, Juju.

00:34:36.600 --> 00:34:40.388
- I wondered if you'd ignore me all night.
- You seemed busy.

00:34:40.560 --> 00:34:42.391
- Congratulations.
- Thanks for coming.

00:34:42.560 --> 00:34:44.152
Can I drive you home?

00:34:44.840 --> 00:34:47.957
- I can walk down the driveway.
- Can I call you?

00:34:48.440 --> 00:34:51.398
Take you out on a real date?
Things have gotten a bit crazy.

00:34:51.560 --> 00:34:54.757
Now, I know I didn't appreciate you.
I want to.

00:34:55.240 --> 00:34:57.800
I want to make you feel appreciated.

00:34:58.240 --> 00:35:02.916
Plan the perfect date, run it by me.
We'll see.

00:35:13.360 --> 00:35:15.191
Come on, man. Her flight leaves soon.

00:35:15.400 --> 00:35:16.913
I'm doing 75 in a 65, all right?

00:35:17.080 --> 00:35:19.514
"I'm doing 75 in a..."
Everyone knows 80 is the new 75.

00:35:19.680 --> 00:35:22.399
- What? Who talks like that?
- What is up with this a.c.?

00:35:22.560 --> 00:35:24.710
My Jewfro is frizzing out.
I look like Screech.

00:35:24.880 --> 00:35:27.189
- The a.c.'s fine.
- What is this music?

00:35:27.480 --> 00:35:30.392
Do not insult Journey. All right?

00:35:36.120 --> 00:35:38.509
- Hey.
- Hey.

00:35:40.000 --> 00:35:41.672
How are you?

00:35:41.840 --> 00:35:46.436
Just embarrassed. I can't believe it,
this huge fight at a fancy party.

00:35:46.600 --> 00:35:49.398
Actually not the first time
that's happened.

00:35:50.320 --> 00:35:53.790
Here. I'm not gonna have time
to get it dry-cleaned before I go.

00:35:54.200 --> 00:35:55.679
Before you go?

00:35:56.160 --> 00:35:59.470
I've been fooling myself thinking
this was gonna be easy.

00:36:00.480 --> 00:36:03.278
I made a huge mess of everything, and...

00:36:03.440 --> 00:36:06.955
...I have this whole life to figure out.
And so does Ryan.

00:36:07.160 --> 00:36:11.199
So take care of him.

00:36:11.360 --> 00:36:13.555
I'll see you.

00:36:28.040 --> 00:36:31.749
I talked to my dad.
He told me what you did.

00:36:31.920 --> 00:36:34.798
Obstructed justice.
Tampered with a witness.

00:36:35.080 --> 00:36:36.752
So, what happens now?

00:36:36.920 --> 00:36:41.118
My guess is, not much. Since it's an
election year, the DA can't afford to lose.

00:36:41.440 --> 00:36:44.159
And without this star witness,
they don't really have a case.

00:36:44.440 --> 00:36:46.715
And if you're gonna go
after the king, Caleb...

00:36:46.880 --> 00:36:49.189
...then you had better know
you can kill the king.

00:36:49.360 --> 00:36:51.430
I told you I didn't want you
to get involved.

00:36:51.600 --> 00:36:55.309
- I do what's best for my family.
- I'd rather go to jail than be responsible...

00:36:55.480 --> 00:36:59.996
...for you being mixed up in this,
getting into bed with my father.

00:37:00.160 --> 00:37:05.234
I promise you, I'd rather send you to jail
than get into bed with your father.

00:37:14.200 --> 00:37:17.715
You do something like this,
there's no going back.

00:37:17.960 --> 00:37:21.509
Yeah. It's kind of like prom night.

00:37:21.680 --> 00:37:23.875
Believe me.

00:37:24.040 --> 00:37:26.998
If anybody's gonna be putting
you in handcuffs...

00:37:27.160 --> 00:37:29.720
...it's gonna be me.

00:37:53.920 --> 00:37:55.638
Anna!

00:37:56.360 --> 00:38:00.148
- Anna, wait.
- Seth? Hold on.

00:38:01.680 --> 00:38:03.875
Seth, what are you doing here?

00:38:04.040 --> 00:38:09.592
Okay. Maybe it's just the champagne
talking, but I'm just gonna say it. Okay?

00:38:10.240 --> 00:38:12.913
- Please do not leave because of me.
- What? What are you...?

00:38:13.080 --> 00:38:15.071
You love me. I read it. And I get it. Okay?

00:38:15.240 --> 00:38:19.279
And I'm so sorry if I did anything
to hurt your feelings. Or cause this.

00:38:19.440 --> 00:38:21.908
But I don't want you to leave.
Okay? None of us do.

00:38:22.080 --> 00:38:25.959
Seth, I love you as a friend.

00:38:26.920 --> 00:38:30.276
- What?
- God, I love you as a friend.

00:38:30.440 --> 00:38:32.715
That doesn't say "Azerbaijan"?

00:38:34.520 --> 00:38:40.755
Look, I think you're an amazing guy.
A little self-absorbed, maybe, but great.

00:38:41.080 --> 00:38:44.755
But, I mean, if there's one thing that
our relationship taught me, it's that...

00:38:44.920 --> 00:38:47.354
...we don't have a lot of chemistry.

00:38:47.560 --> 00:38:49.232
So you're not leaving because of me?

00:38:49.600 --> 00:38:51.955
I'm leaving because I need to leave.

00:38:52.120 --> 00:38:55.669
But who knows? Maybe one day,
we'll be perfect for each other.

00:38:56.400 --> 00:38:58.197
I don't know.

00:38:59.760 --> 00:39:02.718
I do know I have to go to Pittsburgh.

00:39:03.280 --> 00:39:08.638
I'm Ionely, Seth. I thought
I could make this my home, but I can't.

00:39:10.200 --> 00:39:12.509
Thanks for coming...

00:39:14.240 --> 00:39:16.276
...and saying goodbye.

00:39:34.200 --> 00:39:36.316
Anna, wait a second.

00:39:36.560 --> 00:39:39.393
What am I gonna do without you?
Who will I play Jenga with?

00:39:39.560 --> 00:39:42.757
You're so wise. All your sage wisdom.
What am I gonna do without that?

00:39:42.920 --> 00:39:44.512
Confidence, Cohen.

00:39:56.240 --> 00:39:57.389
Anna!

00:40:20.440 --> 00:40:22.670
I'll be right back.

00:40:44.760 --> 00:40:47.957
What if the girl I'm supposed to be with
just went back to Pittsburgh?

00:40:48.120 --> 00:40:50.076
What if she went back to Chino?

00:40:51.080 --> 00:40:53.196
Why would Anna go to Chino?

00:40:54.120 --> 00:40:57.317
- I'm kidding. Come on.
- Nice one.

00:40:57.480 --> 00:41:00.358
Well, at least we have each other.

00:41:00.880 --> 00:41:03.030
Actually, I have Summer now.

00:41:03.200 --> 00:41:06.670
But I'll put a little Seth-Ryan time
on the books.

00:41:06.840 --> 00:41:09.513
- That's quality time.
- Thanks, buddy.

00:41:09.680 --> 00:41:11.875
I could always hang out with Luke.

00:41:12.360 --> 00:41:14.828
What do you think he's doing right now?

00:41:17.320 --> 00:41:19.311
Discovering fire?

00:41:20.200 --> 00:41:22.316
Hunting and gathering?

00:41:23.120 --> 00:41:27.193
Shaving his chest with a Buck Knife?
You guys could do that together.

00:41:27.360 --> 00:41:29.396
I do do that.

00:00:0.500 --> 00:00:2.00
